        ],
        "evidence": [
          "`system/wifi_c2c_service.go` defines mutable globals `c2cServiceFactory`, `connectToWifiForC2C`, and `restartGroundSegForC2C` that determine how `c2cService` is created and how actions execute.",
          "`system/wifi_transport_adapter.go` stores `executeC2CAction` in the adapter struct and initializes it from that global entrypoint, so transport behavior is coupled to package-global state."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Replace mutable package globals with an explicit `c2cDeps` interface/struct passed through constructors (e.g., `newCaptiveTransportAdapter(deps c2cDeps)` and `NewC2CService(deps c2cServiceDeps)`), and use immutable concrete adapters in production.",
        "reasoning": ""
      },
      "status": "fixed",
