      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 3,
      "confidence": "medium",
      "summary": "Runtime code relies on package-level mutable config access, increasing indirection cost and weakening explicit boundaries.",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "design_coherence",
        "related_files": [
          "config/config.go",
          "routines/runtime_seams.go",
          "broadcast/collectors/collectors.go",
          "docker/orchestration/runtime_seams.go"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "`config/config.go` centralizes mutable runtime state and exposes package-global getters/setters used directly by orchestration/routine code.",
          "`routines/runtime_seams.go` and `broadcast/collectors/collectors.go` consume these global values instead of receiving explicit runtime context, so call sites infer behavior indirectly.",
          "The broadcast/runtime seam tests and collectors depend on shared global state in favor of explicit dependencies, creating brittle setup and hidden coupling."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Define an explicit runtime context interface (container paths, architecture, runtime flags, and state snapshots) and thread it through seam constructors; replace most global config reads/writes with injected immutable snapshots plus explicit state update commands.",
