        "evidence": [
          "The same file contains HTTP handler concerns and deep post-upload orchestration (archive extraction, filesystem writes, session validation, provisioning triggers, pier registration, and lifecycle transitions).",
          "Tests target both HTTP-facing behavior and internal orchestration in one area, suggesting the implementation exposes multi-domain behavior without a clear adapter/service split."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Split importer into an HTTP adapter layer and a domain/import service layer: adapter handles request auth/parsing/streaming only, while service handles extraction + configuration pipeline + registration, with explicit interfaces for lifecycle hooks.",
        "reasoning": ""
      },
      "status": "open",
      "note": null,
      "first_seen": "2026-03-01T20:17:36+00:00",
      "last_seen": "2026-03-01T20:17:36+00:00",
      "resolved_at": null,
      "reopen_count": 0,
      "lang": "go",
      "suppressed": false,
      "suppressed_at": null,
      "suppression_pattern": null
    },
    "review::.::holistic::error_consistency::EC-001::faa8c0ab": {
      "id": "review::.::holistic::error_consistency::EC-001::faa8c0ab",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 3,
      "confidence": "high",
      "summary": "`CreateToken` can report success while auth-map registration silently fails.",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "error_consistency",
        "related_files": [
          "auth/auth.go",
          "main.go"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "`CreateToken` calls `AddToAuthMap(conn, token, authed)` and does not check the returned error.",
          "`AddToAuthMap` can return an error (e.g., nil connection path), but callers of `CreateToken` receive only the token/value success result."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Capture and propagate `AddToAuthMap` failures in `CreateToken` with a wrapped error so token issuance and auth-map registration remain atomic from the caller\u2019s perspective.",
        "reasoning": ""
      },
      "status": "open",
      "note": null,
      "first_seen": "2026-03-01T20:17:36+00:00",
      "last_seen": "2026-03-01T20:17:36+00:00",
      "resolved_at": null,
      "reopen_count": 0,
      "lang": "go",
      "suppressed": false,
      "suppressed_at": null,
      "suppression_pattern": null
    },
    "review::.::holistic::error_consistency::EC-002::f1eb640b": {
      "id": "review::.::holistic::error_consistency::EC-002::f1eb640b",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 3,
      "confidence": "high",
      "summary": "Bug-report multipart payload drops field-write and close errors before request dispatch.",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "error_consistency",
        "related_files": [
          "handler/system/support.go",
          "protocol/actions/actions.go"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "`writer.WriteField(\"contact\", contact)` and `writer.WriteField(\"string\", description)` return values are not checked.",
          "`writer.Close()` return value is ignored after all form fields are written.",
          "The request is still sent via `http.NewRequest(http.MethodPost, ...)` even if multipart assembly likely failed."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Check all `WriteField` and `Close` errors, return immediately with context, and avoid sending the request when multipart construction fails.",
        "reasoning": ""
      },
      "status": "open",
      "note": null,
      "first_seen": "2026-03-01T20:17:36+00:00",
      "last_seen": "2026-03-01T20:17:36+00:00",
      "resolved_at": null,
      "reopen_count": 0,
      "lang": "go",
      "suppressed": false,
      "suppressed_at": null,
      "suppression_pattern": null
    },
    "review::.::holistic::error_consistency::EC-003::d743ea16": {
      "id": "review::.::holistic::error_consistency::EC-003::d743ea16",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 3,
      "confidence": "medium",
      "summary": "Network check path discards socket close failures, weakening teardown error guarantees.",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "error_consistency",
        "related_files": [
          "config/config.go",
          "system/system.go"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "`NetCheck` performs network dial, then does `_ = conn.Close()` instead of validating close result.",
          "Resource deallocation errors are the only returned error information here after connection establishment; this reduces observability of edge-case transport lifecycle failures."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Replace underscore assignment with explicit close handling: log/return close errors at least in debug or aggregate with context when close is semantically relevant.",
        "reasoning": ""
      },
      "status": "open",
      "note": null,
      "first_seen": "2026-03-01T20:17:36+00:00",
      "last_seen": "2026-03-01T20:17:36+00:00",
      "resolved_at": null,
      "reopen_count": 0,
      "lang": "go",
